isEmpty().Description: Returns whether this data set contains no data points.

getDataType().Description: Returns the data type this data set represents. All of the data points in the data set are of this data type.

getDataSource().Description: Returns the data source which this data set represents. All of the data points in the data set are from this data source.

getDataPoints().Description: Returns the list of data points represented by this data set. The data points will preserve the same order in which they were inserted. Certain APIs that return a DataSet might insert data points in chronological order, but this isn't enforced.
